(38, 'Hà', 'Hoàng Văn', 'hvha@hcmus.edu.vn', '0369838365', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Phó trưởng khoa', 'I am currently assistant professor in probability and statistics at Faculty of Mathematics and Computer Science, University of Science in Ho Chi Minh city. Before, I was postdoctoral researcher at Laboratoire de Mathématiques Raphaël Salem (LMRS), University of Rouen Normandie (2018 - 2020) and was previously temporary lecturer and research assistant (ATER) at Laboratoire de Mathématiques d\'Orsay, University of Paris-Sud 11 (2017 - 2018).  I obtained my Ph.D. in statistics on the 28th November, 2016 at University Lille 1, France under the supervision of Viet Chi Tran (University Gustave Eiffel), Thanh Mai Pham Ngoc (University Paris - Sud) and Vincent Rivoirard (University Paris Dauphine).       \nĐường dẫn trang cá nhân: https://sites.google.com/view/hoangvanha/home', 'Hoàng Văn Hà.png', 1, 6, NULL, 'TS', 'male', '2024-07-21 19:58:02', '2024-07-25 00:04:33'),
(39, 'Hiên', 'Nguyễn Thị', 'nthien@hcmus.edu.vn', '0448818819', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', 'Hướng nghiên cứu: lý thuyết xác suất, lựa chọn mô hình, thống kê Bayes', 'Nguyễn Thị Hiên.png', 1231321, 6, NULL, 'Th.S', 'female', '2024-07-21 19:59:08', '2024-07-25 00:04:58'),
(40, 'Đạt', 'Nguyễn Tiến', 'ndat@hcmus.edu.vn', '0653541364', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', 'Hướng nghiên cứu:  ước lượng phi tham số, bài toán ngược trong thống kê và statistical learning.', 'Nguyễn Tiến Đạt.JPG', 0, 6, NULL, 'TS', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:00:01', '2024-07-25 00:05:18'),
(41, 'Khánh', 'Tô Đức', 'tdkhanh@hcmus.edu.vn', '0553809413', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', 'I am Khanh, a Lecturer at Department of Probability and Statistics, Faculty of Mathematics and Computer Science, University of Science, Vietnam National University Ho Chi Minh city.\n\nI received my Bachelor’s degree in Oct 2012, after finishing four years of honors program at the Faculty of Mathematics and Computer Science, University of Science, Vietnam National University, Ho Chi Minh city. I graduated top of my class and I did research on mathematical analysis and statistics. After graduating, I was offered a teaching assistant position at the Faculty of Mathematics and Computer Science. During this period, I was fascinated by applications of Statistics in life science. This had motivated me to become a researcher in applied statistics. In 2014, I was selected as a Ph.D. student in Statistics at Department of Statistical Sciences with the first rank in the ranking table of CARIPARO Ph.D. scholarship at the University of Padova, Italy. During three years of my Ph.D. program, I was working hard on the subject “Statistical evaluation of diagnostic tests under verification bias” which is an interested topic in Medical Statistics. I defended my doctoral dissertation in March 2017, and received great appreciation from the committee. The full text of my Ph.D thesis can be found here. In addition, I successful developed an R package (named bcROCsurface) and a web interface to support researchers in the evaluation of predictive ability of diagnostic tests. For these results, I was awarded the Prize for Research 2017 of Department of Statistical Sciences, University of Padova.\n\nFrom May 2017 to June 2022, I was a postdoctoral research fellow at the department and studied on the several research projects with regard to te problem of evaluating the accuracy of diagnostic test (or biomarker, or classifier in general) and meta-analysis. The details of all projects can be found in my CV page. Working on these projects, I gained valuable experience in data analysis for biomedical data and gene expression data, especially for incurable diseases, such as epithelial ovarian cancer, Alzheimer’s disease, type 2 diabetes mellitus, breast cancer. I have accumulated valuable experiences on modeling the model for missing data mechanism and on mixed-effect models, moreover I improved my coding skill in R and C/C++ programming. Last but not least, I understood the important role of diagnostic tests or screening tests (or biomarkers) for early detecting serious diseases, e.g., ovarian cancer, breast cancer and diabetes. These trigger my further research activities in biomedical statistics with regard to evaluating diagnostic tests (screening tests) and cancer research.\n\nBesides doing research, I am also interested in teaching statistics. I am constantly improving my teaching skills to provide the best experience for students of not only statistics but also other majors, for example, biology, medicine, economics, geology.\n\nThe last but not least, I am a an amateur photographer. I like to create photos of natural landscapes or buildings with striking architecture. Soon, I will be sharing my photos on this page.\n\nTrang cá nhân: https://toduckhanh.github.io/', 'Tô Đức Khánh.png', 0, 6, NULL, 'TS', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:00:58', '2024-07-24 23:24:03'),
(42, 'Xuân Mai', 'Lê Thị', 'ltxmai@hcmus.edu.vn', '0820305009', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', NULL, 'person.1024x1024.png', 0, 6, NULL, 'TS', 'female', '2024-07-21 20:01:44', '2024-07-21 20:01:44'),
(43, 'Hồng Nhung', 'Nguyễn Thị', 'nthnhung@hcmus.edu.vn', '0823920022', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', 'Hướng nghiên cứu: thống kê phi tham số, bài toán ngược trong thống kê, chuỗi thời gian', '13.png', 0, 6, NULL, 'Th.S', 'female', '2024-07-21 20:02:23', '2024-07-25 00:05:43'),
(44, 'Thìn', 'Nguyễn Văn', 'nvthin@hcmus.edu.vn', '0816204741', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', 'Hướng nghiên cứu: thống kê nhiều chiều, thống kê Bayes, mô hình hỗn hợp, thống kê môi trường và sinh học, phân tích dữ liệu hàm', '14.png', 0, 6, NULL, 'Th.S', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:03:00', '2024-07-25 00:06:03'),
(45, 'Thanh', 'Đinh Ngọc', 'dnthanh@hcmus.edu.vn', '0626291086', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', 'Hướng nghiên cứu: toán tài chính, xác suất, thống kê ứng dụng', '15.png', 0, 6, NULL, 'PGS.TS', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:08:26', '2024-07-25 00:06:20'),
(46, 'Toàn', 'Nguyễn Hữu', 'nhtoan@hcmus.edu.vn', '0969702791', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', 'Hướng nghiên cứu: toán tài chính, mô hình đánh giá sức khoẻ doanh nghiệp', '17.png', 0, 6, NULL, 'Th.S', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:13:00', '2024-07-25 00:06:33'),
(47, 'Phương', 'Phan Thị', 'phtphuong@hcmus.edu.vn', '0556064830', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', 'Hướng nghiên cứu: toán tài chính, quản lí rủi ro, phân tích tài chính', '18.png', 0, 6, NULL, 'Th.S', 'female', '2024-07-21 20:13:51', '2024-07-25 00:06:48'),
(48, 'Hoàng Anh', 'Nguyễn Lê', 'nlhanh@hcmus.edu.vn', '0821163217', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Trưởng bộ môn', 'I have been working as a lecturer and researcher at Department of Optimization and System Theory, Faculty of Mathematics and Computer Sciences, University of Science - Vietnam National University of Hochiminh City.\n\nMy research interests are connected with Optimization (theory and applications). I focus especially on some topics of Set-Valued Optimization in infinite-dimensional spaces and their applications to several mathematical models.\n\nPlease find my curriculum vitae here.', 'Nguyễn Lê Hoàn Anh.png', 0, 7, NULL, 'PGS.TS', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:14:42', '2024-07-24 23:49:11'),
(49, 'Thuỳ', 'Nguyễn Văn', 'nvthuy@hcmus.edu.vn', '0485679348', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', NULL, 'person.1024x1024.png', 0, 7, NULL, 'Th.S', 'female', '2024-07-21 20:15:24', '2024-07-21 20:15:24'),
(50, 'Thục', 'Cao Nghi', 'cnthuc@hcmus.edu.vn', '0777172288', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', NULL, 'person.1024x1024.png', 0, 7, NULL, 'Th.S', 'female', '2024-07-21 20:16:00', '2024-07-21 20:16:00'),
(51, 'Trọng Long', 'Võ Sĩ', 'vstlong@hcmus.edu.vn', '0969806205', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', NULL, 'person.1024x1024.png', 0, 7, NULL, 'TS', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:16:40', '2024-07-21 20:16:40'),
(52, 'Trường Giang', 'Nguyễn Mạnh', 'nmtgiang@hcmus.edu.vn', '0523657706', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Giảng viên', NULL, 'person.1024x1024.png', 0, 7, NULL, 'Th.S', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:17:22', '2024-07-21 20:17:22'),
(53, 'Bình', 'Nguyễn Thanh', 'ngtbinh@hcmus.edu.vn', '0559130917', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Trưởng bộ môn', 'I was born in Dong Thap, Vietnam, and finished my Ph.D. degree at Ecole Polytechnique in September 2012. My Ph.D. advisor is Professor Denis GREBENKOV. \n\n\nI am an associate professor of computer science and the Head of the Department of Computer Science, Faculty of Mathematics and Computer Science, the University of Science, Vietnam National University in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam. I am the managing director of the AISIA Research Lab for creating the best research environments for students and training excellent new generations in Machine Learning and Data Science in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.\n\n\nI have been organizing a research group on theoretical machine learning with Dinh Cao Duy Thien Vu (Associate Professor, Department of Mathematics, University of Delaware, USA), Lam Si Tung Ho (Associate Professor, Department of Statistics, University of Dalhousie, Canada) and Nguyen Viet Cuong (Applied Scientist, Amazon Inc., USA). \n\n\nUp to now, I have had over 30 students winning Ph.D. fellowships in the top universities in Asia, Europe, and the United States of America.', 'Nguyễn Thanh Bình.jpg', 0, 8, NULL, 'PGS.TS', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:18:14', '2024-07-25 00:07:55'),
(54, 'Thảo', 'Hà Văn', 'hvthao@hcmus.edu.vn', '0199814278', NULL, '1999-01-01', 'Phó trưởng bộ môn', NULL, 'person.1024x1024.png', 0, 8, NULL, 'Th.S', 'male', '2024-07-21 20:19:10', '2024-07-21 20:19:10'),
